// --- Host security scan (one-shot) ---
//
// SecurityScan is the agent-side equivalent of running a curated set
// of host-hardening checks: kernel-version freshness, sysctl posture,
// SSH server config, world-writable / SUID outliers, etc. The set of
// available checks is registered statically inside the agent (see
// internal/agent/security); the request lets the caller restrict the
// scan to a subset by id or category and place an overall deadline on
// the scan.
//
// The response is intentionally a flat list of findings — not a
// pass/fail per check — so a single check can surface multiple
// hardening hits (e.g. one SSH config check returning both
// "PermitRootLogin yes" and "PasswordAuthentication yes") without the
